body:
## Summary
This patch fixes an internal error when selecting a modport on a virtual
interface handle (e.g. `vif.passive_mp`).  The `MemberSel` visitor in
`V3Width.cpp` only handled `AstVar` and `AstClocking` members; an
`AstModport` member hit `v3fatalSrc("MemberSel of non-variable")`.

Discovered during CORE-V-VERIF integration:
https://github.com/openhwgroup/core-v-verif/pull/2724

## Reproducer
```systemverilog
interface my_if(input logic clk);
  logic [7:0] data;
  clocking mon_cb @(posedge clk);
    input data;
  endclocking
  modport passive_mp(clocking mon_cb);
endinterface

class Context;
  virtual my_if vif;
endclass

class Monitor;
  virtual my_if.passive_mp mp;
  function void connect(Context cntxt);
    mp = cntxt.vif.passive_mp;
  endfunction
endclass

module t;
  logic clk = 0;
  always #5 clk = ~clk;
  my_if vif(.clk(clk));
  initial begin
    automatic Context c = new;
    automatic Monitor m = new;
    c.vif = vif;
    m.connect(c);
    $write("*-* All Finished *-*\n");
    $finish;
  end
endmodule
```

On master:
```
%Error: Internal Error: V3Width.cpp:3523: MemberSel of non-variable
```

## Changes
- `V3Width.cpp`: add `AstModport` branch in the `MemberSel` / `IfaceRefDType` visitor — replace MemberSel with its `fromp` operand re-typed to a modport-qualified `AstIfaceRefDType`

## Test
- Added `test_regress/t/t_interface_virtual_modport_sel.{v,py}` — chain access (`cntxt.vif.passive_mp`), direct access (`tmp.passive_mp`), active/passive/signal modports, clocking-block read, multi-cycle data propagation

